OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1780185774
OL,3,CBreast cancer patient spared chemo
OL,4,Cthrough trial says it felt 'like
OL,5,CChristmas'
OL,7,FA woman who took part in a study which
OL,8,Ffound some people with breast cancer
OL,9,Fcan safely avoid chemotherapy said
OL,10,Freceiving the news she did not need
OL,11,Fthe treatment felt "like Christmas".
OL,13,FMother-of-two Karen Bonham, from
OL,14,FCardiff, took part in an international
OL,15,Fclinical trial led by University
OL,16,FCollege London (UCL), designed to
OL,17,Fidentify patients who could be spared
OL,18,Fthe "physical and emotional burden of
OL,19,Fchemotherapy".
OL,26,@sD@TOUsD@cO]zD@EOU{D@MO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31102
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1780185774
OL,3,CBreast cancer patient spared chemo
OL,4,Cthrough trial says it felt 'like
OL,5,CChristmas'
OL,7,FThe study followed more than 4,400
OL,8,Fpatients aged 40 and over across the
OL,9,FUK, Norway, Sweden, Australia, New
OL,10,FZealand and Thailand.
OL,12,FIt used a gene test called Prosigna to
OL,13,Fmeasure the activity of genes involved
OL,14,Fin breast cancer growth.
OL,16,FResults suggest those aged 40 and over
OL,17,Fwhose tumours had a low Prosigna test
OL,18,Fscore ` more than two-thirds of those
OL,19,Fwho took part in the study ` can be
OL,20,Fsafely treated with hormone therapy
OL,21,Falone.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31103
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1780185774
OL,3,CBreast cancer patient spared chemo
OL,4,Cthrough trial says it felt 'like
OL,5,CChristmas'
OL,7,FThe trial was designed to find out
OL,8,Fwhether this method would lead to a
OL,9,F"meaningful increase" in the number of
OL,10,Fpatients whose cancer returned or died
OL,11,Fwithin five years.
OL,13,FIt found chemotherapy had "little or
OL,14,Fno additional benefit", as outcomes
OL,15,Fwere similar regardless of whether the
OL,16,Ftreatment was used.
OL,18,FRegularly offered to people with early-
OL,19,Fstage breast cancer that has spread to
OL,20,Fthe nearby lymph nodes, chemotherapy
OL,21,Flowers the risk of it returning.
OL,26,@qD@AOUqD@UO]uD@[OUvD@VO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31104
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1780185774
OL,3,CBreast cancer patient spared chemo
OL,4,Cthrough trial says it felt 'like
OL,5,CChristmas'
OL,7,FBut it comes with significant side
OL,8,Feffects and clinicians are concerned
OL,9,Fit offers little benefit to those with
OL,10,Fthe most common, hormone-sensitive
OL,11,Ftype of breast cancer, UCL said.
OL,13,FThe university said researchers
OL,14,Festimate more than 5,000 NHS patients
OL,15,Fa year could avoid chemotherapy thanks
OL,16,Fto the trial.
OL,18,FAfter being diagnosed with breast
OL,19,Fcancer following a routine screening
OL,20,Fin June 2017, Ms Bonham was "dreading"
OL,21,Fthe prospect of chemotherapy.
OL,26,@|D@]OU|D@fO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31105
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1780185774
OL,3,CBreast cancer patient spared chemo
OL,4,Cthrough trial says it felt 'like
OL,5,CChristmas'
OL,7,FMs Bonham, who worked as a speech and
OL,8,Flanguage therapist for four decades,
OL,9,Fagreed to take part in the trial in
OL,10,Fthe hope that she could avoid
OL,11,Fchemotherapy.
OL,13,FThe 64-year-old had already cut her
OL,14,Fhair short when she got the news she
OL,15,Fwould not require the treatment, while
OL,16,Fwalking on a beach.
OL,18,FMs Bonham said: "How to describe the
OL,19,Finitial feeling? Immense relief? Like
OL,20,FChristmas? Certainly a mixture of the
OL,21,Ftwo."
OL,26,@zD@QOU}D@EO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
